-- National Bank of Abu Dhabi to Consider Bond Sale in Australian, NZ Dollars
-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 2010-10-17T05:59:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-17/national-bank-of-abu-dhabi-to-consider-bond-sale-in-australian-nz-dollars.html
National Bank of Abu Dhabi PJSC, the
United Arab Emirates’ second-largest lender, said its board will
consider selling bonds under its Australian and New Zealand
dollar medium-term note program.  The board will meet on Oct. 26 and the bond program was
approved by the bank’s annual general meeting in December 2007,
the lender said in a statement to the Abu Dhabi bourse today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shaji Mathew in Dubai at 
